Can you please put this into a sentence, •	Due diligence study of the site/building to identify any issues that may increase the risk and or cost of the project, for example:
o	Title search to check ownership of the site and any encumbrances such as easements, or restrictions, for example: multiple ownership, requirements under a 173 Agreement with the Municipal Council, caveats;
o	Cadastral survey to show boundaries of the lot or lots, and to plot the title search information, including surrounding properties;
o	Topographical survey including contours, site orientation and dimensions, site features for example: underground and overhead service locations, existing trees, existing buildings, car parking spaces, 
o	Geotechnical investigation to check soil type and bearing pressure of underlying geomorphology and water table;
o	Drainage and flood assessment to check flooding, for example: 1 in 100-year flood incidence level (or the chance of a flood reaching this level every 100 years: in this case 1% incidence);
o	Land use requirements such as land zoning with limitations on sub-division, density, uses, height, set-backs, car parking and other rules;
o	Biodiversity study to check on the presence of rare and endangered species of flora and fauna and protection requirements;
o	Net gain requirements for vegetation removal as required by Municipal Councils
o	Indigenous and non-indigenous heritage requirements, for example: protection of archaeological sites, buildings, trees, views, monuments;
o	Environmental investigation to check for possible soil and water contamination, buried waste, fuel or septic tanks;
o	Municipal council assets – their existence and condition, for example: stormwater drains, drain covers, roads, kerbs and gutters, footpaths and crossovers, fences nature strips, signs, bollards, bins and seats;
o	Utility provider above ground assets – for example gas meters, fire hydrants, electricity sub-stations, poles, wires and streetlights, traffic lights and controllers; 
o	Traffic management requirements for the site and surrounds including car parking requirements;
o	Supply Authority services for water, sewer, gas, electricity, communications;
o	Legal checks to determine any existing legal agreements that cover the site or building.
